comment: Jackson's (DET) incidental contact does not affect Brooks' (CHI) ability to defend.
Gasol (CHI) and Gibson (CHI) make incidental contact as they legally contest Drummond's (DET) reverse layup attempt.
Drummond (DET) bumps Brooks (CHI) and the contact affects his RSBQ.
Gibson (CHI) sets the screen on Jackson (DET) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Jackson (DET) and Gibson (CHI) briefly engage while setting up for rebounding position.
Williams (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Brooks' (CHI) drive to the basket.
Butler (CHI) hand checks Jackson (DET) on the perimeter.
Noah (CHI) jumps forward into Drummond (DET) and affects his shot at the basket.
Drummond's (DET) contact does not affect Gasol's (CHI) RSBQ.
Drummond (DET) makes contact to Gasol's (CHI) body on the successful putback dunk.
Moore (CHI) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (DET) jump shot.
Drummond (DET) commits a take foul on Mirotic (CHI).
